   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>The check box in the <uicontrol>Is Active?</uicontrol> column of the user account is cleared.</li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>You can activate an inactive user account to allow a user access to the application. On activating an account, the user can log in to the application. </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol>User Management</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol>User Accounts</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>USER ACCOUNTS</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the appropriate deactivated user account.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Mark Active/Inactive</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>Alternatively, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the required inactive user account, and then click <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The <uicontrol>EDIT USER</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>From the <uicontrol>Status</uicontrol> drop-down list, select <uicontrol>Active</uicontrol>.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Click  <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
